H0.text: In November 1935, which British prime minister returned to office after a general election. Ramsay MacDonald

H1.text: In November 1935, which British prime minister returned to office after a general election. Neville Chamberlain

H2.text: In November 1935, which British prime minister returned to office after a general election. Winston Churchill

H3.text: In November 1935, which British prime minister returned to office after a general election. Stanley Baldwin

A4.text: In 1935, Baldwin replaced MacDonald as prime minister and won the 1935 general election with another large majority.

A5.text: Stanley Baldwin was Prime Minister from June 1935 to May 1937.
